In perfect shape and on time. Love The January Man.  Fatal Instinct is a parody of murder movies and for the first few minutes there are some cute gags, but it gets boring and stupid in a big hurry.
January Man has been knocked by critics.  I found it to be funny and exciting.  Went into my large collection.

"January Man" is an excellent piece of work, with a superb cast and excellent performances. It is both entertaining and heartwarming. If I had several appendages, I'd give this film 8 thumbs up!
"Fatal Instinct" has its humorous moments, but is so-so at best. However, "January Man" makes this item well worth the price!
great  flick
I enjoy most of the spoof movies and this is no exception. The fact that I was also able to get January Man was a definite bonus!

I purchased this for "Fatal Instinct," which is one hilarious movie that pokes fun at other serious suspense movies out around or before the time (like "Basic Instinct," "Sleeping With the Enemy" and "Fatal Attraction"). I'd forgotten just how funny it was and it is great to see a serious actor like Armand Assante out of character, loosening up in his role.
I found "January Man" somewhat entertaining but not as much a comedy. Mary Elizabeth Mastrantonio is a joy to watch and fans of the late Alan Rickman will not be disappointed with his role in it.
